{"title":"3T’s 1st Made-in-Italy eBike is new Racemax Boost Italia Integrale with No Visible Cables","link":"https://bikerumor.com/3t-racemax-boost-italia-integrale-made-in-italy-gravel-ebike/","date":1698944400000,"content":"<p><img width=\"6827\" height=\"4308\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully--e1698931187136.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale fully\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully--e1698931187136.jpeg 6827w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully--e1698931187136-297x187.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully--e1698931187136-800x505.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully--e1698931187136-120x76.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully--e1698931187136-768x485.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully--e1698931187136-1536x969.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully--e1698931187136-2048x1292.jpeg 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Much lighter than ever, this new 3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale ebike takes all the Italian-made gravel style and new full cable integration from the latest Exploro Racemax Italia Integrale and adds upgraded Mahle power. The newest ebike in the 3T line-up is their first made in-house in their Bergamo, Italy factory. And it adds the smooth pedal-assist power boost of the well-known Mahle X-20 system to deliver a fast and lightweight gravel machine. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-clearance--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-clearance--800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale clearance\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-clearance--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-clearance--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-clearance--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-clearance--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-clearance--1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-clearance--2048x1365.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-clearance--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>All Photos/3T</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>How lightweight?<em> </em> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Project X super build comes in sub-11kg (24.25lb) in size 54 without pedals. That’s a full kilo and a half lighter than the last generation we tested a couple of seasons back!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully-edited.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully-edited-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale fully\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully-edited-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully-edited-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully-edited-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-fully-edited-768x512.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>What is the 3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale gravel ebike?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The 3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale is the ebike version of the 3T Exploro RaceMax. This model is the second generation of the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-3t-e-exploro-racemax-will-boost-your-e-bike-gravel-range-and-your-average-speed/\">3T RaceMax Boost (reviewed here)</a>. The updated frame boasts entirely internal cable routing and optimized aerodynamics.  Plus — it is 3T’s first ebike manufactured in its Italian facility. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-power-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-power--800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale power\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-power--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-power--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-power--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-power--768x512.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For those unfamiliar, the Racemax is a 3Ts’ aero gravel race machine, focused on race performance and efficiency. The 3T Racemax frame takes a practical gravel look at aerodynamics. The 3T engineering team even incorporated larger gravel tires into the overall aero picture, gifting the bike more real-world performance. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem-details-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem-details--800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale stem details\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem-details--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem-details--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem-details--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem-details--768x512.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem--800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale stem\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-stem--768x512.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame boasts super-clean cable routing, that dovetails with 3Ts’ latest stem, the ‘More Integrale.’ The stem and bars are highly adjustable, allowing easy changes to cockpit height and length without cutting and replacing brake cables. To learn more about the 3T Racemax, check our in-depth <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-3t-exploro-racemax-hones-aero-gravel-with-wide-tire-specific-aerodynamics/#comment-3425492\">news piece here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-down-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-down--800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale down\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-down--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-down--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-down--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-down--768x512.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>3T — Made (lighter) in Italy</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/3t-exploro-italia-gravel-bikes-upgraded-fully-internal-cable-routing/\">3T is committed to Italian manufacturing</a>. Each Racemax Italia frame is 100% made directly above the offices of the company headquarters in their in-house production facilities.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-crankset-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-crankset--800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale crankset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-crankset--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-crankset--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-crankset--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-crankset--768x512.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>By producing the Racemax Boost Italia in-house in Bergamo, 3T can produce an ebike frame weighing 1000g (unpainted, +/- 3%). It’s not just weight that in-house manufacturing optimizes. 3T says the Italian-made Racemax Boost Italia frame has a bottom bracket that is 9% stiffer relative to the RaceMax frame produced in Asia.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-chainstay-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-chainstay--800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale chainstay\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-chainstay--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-chainstay--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-chainstay--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-chainstay--768x512.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Mahle X-20 Customizable Power</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Mahle X-20 engine provides 55Nm of power to the new 3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale — but only when the user needs it. The Mahle X-20 engine employs a torque and cadence sensor in the bottom bracket. Depending on their needs and the ride ahead, riders can customize the power profile.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-rear-brake--scaled.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-rear-brake--800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale rear brake\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-rear-brake--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-rear-brake--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-rear-brake--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-rear-brake--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-rear-brake--1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-rear-brake--2048x1365.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-rear-brake--720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>What does that mean in real ride terms?</em> The 236 Wh battery allows a rider of 75kg (165 lbs) to ride 100km (62 miles) with 1500 m (about 4900ft.) of climbing. But if you want to extend the range further, there is an optional battery extender. This extra battery extender is below the downtube, near the charging port. It also doesn’t take up any valuable water bottle space like other range extenders. The Mahle X-20 range extender allows riders to carry two bottles in the main triangle.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale Sizing</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Racemax Boost Italia Ardesia and Project X nude carbon versions come in four sizes from 51 to 58. Both are spec’d with SRAM Rival XPLR and Red, respectively. Both versions boast carbon 3T “super-wide” 45 | 40 LTD rims, with the Project X featuring a 3T Torno crank. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-seat-tube-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-seat-tube--800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale seat tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-seat-tube--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-seat-tube--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-seat-tube--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/3T-Racemax-Boost-Italia-Integrale-seat-tube--768x512.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>3T Racemax Boost Italia Integrale Builds and Pricing</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Ardesia</strong> <strong>Build</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spec: </strong>SRAM Rival XPLR 1×12, carbon 3T 45 | 40 LTD “super-wide”</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> $8,851 / €7,376 / £6,877 VAT excluded in Europe and Asia</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong> “Project X”</strong> <strong>Build</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spec:</strong> SRAM Red AXS 1×12, carbon 3T 45 | 40 LTD “super-wide” rims, 3T Torno crank, and San Marco 3D printed carbon saddle.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> $12,786 / €10,655 / £9,926 VAT excluded in Europe and Asia </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.3t.bike/en/\" target=\"_blank\">3T.bike</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/3t-racemax-boost-italia-integrale-made-in-italy-gravel-ebike/\">3T’s 1st Made-in-Italy eBike is new Racemax Boost Italia Integrale with No Visible Cables</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d16ef3bb5286bff2cc521d1cc60722e7af1675ded80fdf7f80e768928df10c4a","category":"Cycling"}